4.GMC

find the optimal subset of X which make the \(GMC(Y|X_{sub})\) or \(GMC(Y|G(X_{sub}))\) largest!

source("GMC.R")
GMC
## function (data, nlocal = 25) 
## {
##     x = data[, 1]
##     y = data[, 2]
##     n = length(x)
##     ln = nlocal
##     xdata = data[order(data[, 1]), ]
##     ydata = data[order(data[, 2]), ]
##     E_xy = rep(0, n)
##     E_yx = rep(0, n)
##     X = t(matrix(rep(xdata[, 1], n), ncol = n))
##     X = 1/(1 + abs(X - t(X)))
##     Y = t(matrix(rep(ydata[, 2], n), ncol = n))
##     Y = 1/(1 + abs(Y - t(Y)))
##     for (i in 1:n) {
##         li = max(1, i - ln)
##         ui = min(n, i + ln)
##         E_yx[i] = sum(X[i, li:ui] * xdata[li:ui, 2])/sum(X[i, 
##             li:ui])
##         E_xy[i] = sum(Y[i, li:ui] * ydata[li:ui, 1])/sum(Y[i, 
##             li:ui])
##     }
##     GMC = c(var(E_xy)/var(x), var(E_yx)/var(y))
##     return(GMC)
## }
